==English==

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# {{lb|en|of a|person or animal}} Unable to distinguish between two or more primary colors (usually red and green).
# {{lb|en|of a|person or process}} Holding no prejudice based on skin color or [[race]]; not paying attention to skin color.
#* {{quote-book|en|title=The New Jim Crow|author=Michelle Alexander|year=2012|ISBN=9781595586438|page=183
|passage=Because mass incarceration is officially '''colorblind''', it seems inconceivable that the system could function much like a racial caste system.}}

